PrecisAmendments to the LICENSING AND ARBITRATION REGULATIONS which set out in detail the kind of information that must be provided with an application for a dealer's licence, establish more objective criteria for the issuance, refusal, suspension or cancellation of a licence or for the bonding of dealers, and prescribe a fee of $400 for filing a complaint with the Board of Arbitration.
